data.name: lblAboutProgramText.Text
data.value: Data Studio is a open code project to play and investigate with NoSQL different databases. With this program you can create collections and documents, work with some operations, execute some simple queries and save your work in a json file. Finally, you can download and check the source code to learn about interesting patterns of data access.

data.name: lblAboutMeText.Text
data.value: I´m Fernando Concepción Gutiérrez, Senior Computer Engineer, titulated from "Universidad Complutense de Madrid" and a specialist and lover of Microsoft technologies. From the beginning of my career, I have specialized me in Microsoft technologies and in architectures, especially in the .NET framework. I´m interested about architectures, their designs, their development phases, design patterns, clean programming, database design, management and use; but also I´m interested about relational and non-relational databases, their use with Entity Framework and Code First, MVC, Web Api, Azure, good practices, design patterns (dependency management, layer separation, clean code ...).
